<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- Pickup: I root pos (D-A-D), open 5th RH — gentle, light entry
- m1 (A-E-A-D): V and II alternate per beat; LH open 5ths throughout; RH follows chord changes in parallel 3rds/6ths
- m2 (G-C#°-D): IV on beats 1-2 with long tone, vii° passing eighth, I resolves; LH G-D-G quartal then C#°-E-A diminished color
- m3 (Bm-F#m-A-D): All 4 chords per quarter; minor colors with open 4th+4th LH voicings (B-F#-B, F#-C#-F#) giving quartal texture
- m4 (D-Em-Bm7): I rich with 3rd in top LH voice; ii passing; vi7 adds emotional weight mid-phrase
- m5 (Bm-G-A): vi high on RH (D5-F#5 open 6th); IV full triad; V held half on both hands — builds toward repeat
- m6 (Bm-E→V-A-D): vi then V substitute for non-diatonic E; V cadences with leading tone C#; I resolve
- m7 (F#m-G-D-A): iii quartal LH (F#-C#-F# = two 4ths); IV quartal G-D-G; I richest voicing (4 notes LH); V light 2-note
- m8 (G-D-A-D): Final authentic cadence IV-I-V-I; LH converges to root pos; RH narrows to unison D4

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- Inner line in LH: A2→G2→F#2→E2→F#2→... smooth stepwise descent mirrors soprano descent
- RH alto line: C#5→B4→A4→G4→F#4 stepwise descending across mm.1-4 — mirrors tenor
- vii° in m2 uses chromatic passing motion C#3-E3-A3 — brief diminished color
- m7 beat 3 LH has 4 notes (D2-A2-D3-F#3) = "333" pattern = richest point before final cadence

TEXTURE ARC:
- Opening (m0-m1): 3 LH + 2 RH notes — lightest
- Development (m2-m4): 3 LH + 2-3 RH, rhythmic variety (dotted quarters + eighths)
- Climax (m5-m7): 3-4 LH notes, iii quartal color, full IV-I-V-I progression
- Final cadence (m8): Settles to root position I (D2-A2-D3-F#3), RH narrows to single D4
-->
